{{one source|date=September 2013}} [[Image:Memorial of Murato on Pelister.JPG|300px|thumb|right|Memorial of Dimitar Ilievski - Murato on [[Pelister]] near the dormitory "Kopanki".]]
'''Dimitar Ilievski - Murato''' ({{lang-mk|Димитар Илиевски - Мурато}}) (1953 in [[Bitola]] &ndash; May 10, 1989 in [[Mount Everest]]) was an alpinist from the [[Republic of Macedonia]] representing [[SFR Yugoslavia]], the first [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonian]] ever to climb the highest peak of the world, [[Mount Everest]]. He died on the descent of Mt. Everest.
Murato, as he was known in his native town [[Bitola]], reached the top of [[Mount Everest]] on May 10, 1989 as part of a larger [[SFR Yugoslavia|Yugoslavian]] expedition, of which only few alpinists succeeded to reach the peak. He is noted as the 264th summiter of [[Mount Everest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everesthistory.com/everestsummits/summits89.htm|title=List of climbers who conquered Mount Everest in 1989|publisher=EverestHistory|accessdate=2008-07-01}}</ref>
After reaching the summit, he put the flags of both former [[SFR Yugoslavia]] and [[SR Macedonia]].
In his honour, a traditional memorial march to [[Pelister]] named after him is organized every year around the date of his biggest achievement and tragedy.
